1. command to create topic

gcloud pubsub topics create emp-trans-stream-topic

2. create dataset in BQ

bq mk --dataset --location=us-central1 emp_trans_dataset

3. create table 

bq mk --table emp_trans_dataset.emp_stream_table \
emp_id:INT64,name:STRING,dept:STRING,sal:INT64

4. create temp bucket

gsutil mb -l us-central1 gs://dataflowtempbucket7

5. Crate dataflow staging bucket

gsutil mb -l us-central1 gs://dataflowstaging7


7. open the cloud shell -click ... (three dots on top right) upload dataflow.py file

7. script to run dataflow job

python dataflow_trans.py \
  --runner=DataflowRunner \
  --project=ranjanrishi-project \
  --region=us-central1 \
  --temp_location=gs://dataflowtempbucket7 \
  --staging_location=gs://dataflowstaging7 \
  --streaming
  
8. execute the data_gen_script.py to generate the streaming data and publish it to topic  

8. post run execute the below query to verify the dataflow

select * from emp_dataset.emp_stream_table where 1=1;

9. check the streaming job is running status

gcloud dataflow jobs list --region=us-central1

10. command used to stop the streaming job (#get the job id from above command) 

gcloud dataflow jobs cancel <JOB_ID> --region=us-central1 

gcloud dataflow jobs drain <JOB_ID> --region=us-central1 (recomended stop once all published messages are loaded)

